notes: S Chanderpaul 50, 55 minutes, 47 balls 2 x 4, 3 x 6
West Indies innings: 1x5 ball over (44th over, Kallis 8th over, called by Umpire Mack)

milestones.description: Kallis and Gibbs's 179-run partnership is SA's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 172 between Gary Kirsten and Kallis

stories.title: South Africa level series at 1-1
stories.summary: The high-quality fielding and the controlled bowling the West Indies exhibited at Sabina Park last weekend were nowhere to be seen at the Antigua Recreation Ground here yesterday

stories.title: Gibbs century lifts South Africa to eight-wicket win in Antigua ODI
stories.summary:
A South African record second wicket stand of 179 between Herschelle Gibbs
and Jacques Kallis proved the undoing of the West Indies as South Africa won
the second one-day international by eight wickets at the Antigua Recreation
Ground and levelled
